1
00:01:06,336 --> 00:01:10,778
=The Truth=

2
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:14,136
=Episode 23=

3
00:01:15,566 --> 00:01:16,527
Victim Liu Min,

4
00:01:16,646 --> 00:01:18,006
female, 47 years old,

5
00:01:18,247 --> 00:01:18,807
from Yushan,

6
00:01:19,247 --> 00:01:20,607
with theft and fraud convictions

7
00:01:21,247 --> 00:01:23,807
and wanted by police for multiple counts
of child trafficking.

8
00:01:24,406 --> 00:01:26,406
She used a lost ID card.

9
00:01:27,167 --> 00:01:30,126
Liu Jianyuan's DNA
was found under her fingernails.

10
00:01:30,447 --> 00:01:32,047
Suspected to be from a struggle.

11
00:01:33,327 --> 00:01:34,206
Liu Jianyuan,

12
00:01:34,366 --> 00:01:35,807
male, 46 years old,

13
00:01:36,006 --> 00:01:37,167
also from Yushan.

14
00:01:38,206 --> 00:01:39,766
He served time for robbery and assault.

15
00:01:40,926 --> 00:01:43,406
Like Liu Min, he's also a suspect

16
00:01:43,486 --> 00:01:44,687
of child trafficking.

17
00:01:46,126 --> 00:01:47,607
So they were both traffickers.

18
00:01:47,926 --> 00:01:50,006
So it was criminals
turning on each other.

19
00:01:50,006 --> 00:01:51,047
Total infighting.

20
00:01:52,006 --> 00:01:52,607
Wait.

21
00:01:52,607 --> 00:01:54,687
We're not sure
it was definitely Liu Jianyuan.

22
00:01:55,006 --> 00:01:55,807
Well...

23
00:01:57,447 --> 00:02:00,447
Surveillance footage captured
Liu Jianyuan entering the hotel.

24
00:02:00,887 --> 00:02:02,167
At 6 PM two days ago,

25
00:02:02,167 --> 00:02:04,366
Liu Jianyuan entered
through the hotel's main entrance.

26
00:02:04,447 --> 00:02:06,967
He passed the front desk,
took the elevator to the sixth floor,

27
00:02:07,967 --> 00:02:09,086
and went to Room 601.

28
00:02:09,086 --> 00:02:10,407
Liu Min opened the door for him.

29
00:02:10,766 --> 00:02:14,447
Later, Liu Min went downstairs
to get food and returned to the room.

30
00:02:14,526 --> 00:02:18,447
The next time Liu Jianyuan was caught
on camera was at 2:10 AM yesterday

31
00:02:18,646 --> 00:02:20,407
when he left the room.

32
00:02:20,686 --> 00:02:21,887
He didn't take the elevator.

33
00:02:22,047 --> 00:02:25,407
Instead, he took
the unmonitored fire escape stairs down

34
00:02:25,607 --> 00:02:27,526
and left
through the back-door parking lot.

35
00:02:30,727 --> 00:02:31,727
Surveillance shows

36
00:02:31,966 --> 00:02:33,287
that Rose Garden Hotel's Room 601

37
00:02:33,287 --> 00:02:36,206
had no one else enter
besides Liu Min and Liu Jianyuan.

38
00:02:36,607 --> 00:02:37,567
During the crime's

39
00:02:37,926 --> 00:02:38,926
estimated time,

40
00:02:39,167 --> 00:02:42,287
the front desk called Room 601
due to a noise complaint.

41
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:43,447
A man answered.

42
00:02:44,646 --> 00:02:46,686
Has Liu Min's phone been found?

43
00:02:46,806 --> 00:02:47,727
Not yet.

44
00:02:48,727 --> 00:02:51,766
These two traffickers came to Yunxi
surely not to commit crimes again?

45
00:02:53,526 --> 00:02:55,086
I've hit another dead end.

46
00:02:55,366 --> 00:02:56,926
The train station is right next door.

47
00:02:56,926 --> 00:02:58,686
If they bought tickets
and boarded a train,

48
00:02:58,847 --> 00:03:00,366
they probably used fake IDs too.

49
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:03,366
Where do we go from here?

50
00:03:05,246 --> 00:03:07,007
The train station
is literally steps away.

51
00:03:07,127 --> 00:03:09,407
Most motorcycle taxis
wouldn't take such a short fare.

52
00:03:09,727 --> 00:03:11,727
Especially for a place you can walk to.

53
00:03:12,086 --> 00:03:13,966
From Liu Jianyuan's perspective,

54
00:03:13,966 --> 00:03:16,086
whether for cost or safety,

55
00:03:16,327 --> 00:03:18,486
taking a motorcycle taxi
shouldn't have been necessary.

56
00:03:19,526 --> 00:03:23,646
Captain Leng, I think we should
first find that motorcycle taxi driver

57
00:03:23,966 --> 00:03:26,447
and figure out Liu Jianyuan's
whereabouts ASAP.

58
00:03:26,646 --> 00:03:30,047
We must check Liu Min's ticket purchases
using Mai Qianqian's ID.

59
00:03:30,486 --> 00:03:32,246
They both stayed near the train station.

60
00:03:32,246 --> 00:03:33,766
They might have arrived by train

61
00:03:33,766 --> 00:03:34,806
or be leaving by train.

62
00:03:34,966 --> 00:03:38,447
If tickets were bought online, we should
be able to find Liu Min's phone number.

63
00:03:39,486 --> 00:03:40,607
Not bad, Wang Tong.

64
00:03:40,926 --> 00:03:42,486
Your analysis is spot on.

65
00:03:42,486 --> 00:03:43,327
Get moving.

66
00:03:48,792 --> 00:03:57,206
(Yunxi)

67
00:03:57,206 --> 00:03:58,526
This is way too blurry.

68
00:03:58,526 --> 00:04:00,167
I can't make out the face at all.

69
00:04:01,447 --> 00:04:03,287
The bike's common
without a license plate.

70
00:04:03,447 --> 00:04:04,607
Our bikes all look the same.

71
00:04:04,766 --> 00:04:06,206
There's no way to tell who's who.

72
00:04:06,206 --> 00:04:07,047
Exactly.

73
00:04:07,206 --> 00:04:09,447
So many guys
work the train station area alone.

74
00:04:09,646 --> 00:04:11,007
Can't help you, officer.

75
00:04:13,086 --> 00:04:14,806
Everyone, listen up.
No need to be nervous.

76
00:04:15,127 --> 00:04:17,287
We're looking for this driver

77
00:04:17,607 --> 00:04:19,047
to gather passenger info.

78
00:04:19,167 --> 00:04:20,167
Nothing else.

79
00:04:25,326 --> 00:04:26,847
Let me share a bit more.

80
00:04:27,366 --> 00:04:30,087
The man we're looking for
is a human trafficker.

81
00:04:30,806 --> 00:04:31,607
A human trafficker?

82
00:04:33,727 --> 00:04:35,207
You cops have to tell the truth.

83
00:04:35,647 --> 00:04:37,207
Don't worry, I guarantee it.

84
00:04:39,767 --> 00:04:42,006
The driver you're looking for
is from my hometown.

85
00:04:42,527 --> 00:04:44,006
I'll text him to come over.

86
00:04:51,926 --> 00:04:53,167
I remember that guy.

87
00:04:53,926 --> 00:04:55,207
That early morning,

88
00:04:56,207 --> 00:04:57,686
he got on at Rose Garden's back door.

89
00:04:58,607 --> 00:05:02,207
I'd just dropped off someone
rushing for a train

90
00:05:02,686 --> 00:05:05,287
and was thinking of resting
inside the station

91
00:05:05,607 --> 00:05:06,686
and grabbing a bite.

92
00:05:08,486 --> 00:05:10,407
So, do you remember where you took him?

93
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:12,632
Tech University Staff Community.

94
00:05:13,486 --> 00:05:14,287
Not exactly close.

95
00:05:15,126 --> 00:05:16,486
But he paid well,

96
00:05:16,486 --> 00:05:17,647
so I took the fare.

97
00:05:18,607 --> 00:05:20,246
Remember anything more specific?

98
00:05:20,527 --> 00:05:21,647
Building? Apartment?

99
00:05:24,167 --> 00:05:26,407
That community
doesn't let outside vehicles in.

100
00:05:26,607 --> 00:05:28,967
About which building, I...

101
00:05:29,967 --> 00:05:31,767
I just remember him making a call

102
00:05:32,287 --> 00:05:33,967
and telling me to stop
at the north gate.

103
00:05:34,527 --> 00:05:36,407
Was it Building 11

104
00:05:36,407 --> 00:05:38,566
or Building 17?

105
00:05:39,686 --> 00:05:41,006
That guy's accent was too thick.

106
00:05:41,167 --> 00:05:42,407
I didn't catch it clearly.

107
00:05:43,006 --> 00:05:43,806
Thank you.

108
00:05:56,767 --> 00:05:59,647
Property management said
Building 17 is near the north gate.

109
00:06:00,246 --> 00:06:01,566
Residents of Building 11 usually

110
00:06:01,566 --> 00:06:03,087
don't use the farther north gate.

111
00:06:03,806 --> 00:06:06,246
Building 17 has four entrances.

112
00:06:06,486 --> 00:06:08,207
Five floors make it
20 households in total.

113
00:06:08,607 --> 00:06:09,607
If we do a full sweep...

114
00:06:09,607 --> 00:06:11,207
A full sweep isn't practical.

115
00:06:11,686 --> 00:06:15,607
We might alert Liu Jianyuan
if he's here.

116
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:26,207
Let's go check it out.

117
00:06:30,806 --> 00:06:31,967
I called the police.

118
00:06:32,366 --> 00:06:33,207
I didn't do it.

119
00:06:33,207 --> 00:06:33,847
City CID.

120
00:06:33,847 --> 00:06:35,446
I came up to have dinner with my friend.

121
00:06:35,736 --> 00:06:37,496
Opening the door,
I found him on the floor.

122
00:06:37,496 --> 00:06:38,847
Blood was on the floor and walls.

123
00:06:38,847 --> 00:06:41,047
I... I really don't know what happened.

124
00:06:41,806 --> 00:06:42,647
City CID.

125
00:06:42,647 --> 00:06:43,407
What happened?

126
00:06:44,287 --> 00:06:45,246
We received a report.

127
00:06:45,246 --> 00:06:46,767
It's said someone died upstairs.

128
00:06:46,767 --> 00:06:47,686
He reported it.

129
00:06:48,647 --> 00:06:50,607
My friend was killed up there.

130
00:06:50,607 --> 00:06:51,407
It's all over...

131
00:06:51,886 --> 00:06:52,647
Your friend's name?

132
00:06:52,967 --> 00:06:53,967
Liu Jianyuan.

133
00:06:57,167 --> 00:06:58,926
You should go up and see.

134
00:06:58,926 --> 00:07:00,167
It's too horrible.

135
00:07:00,566 --> 00:07:01,287
It's Room 502.

136
00:07:01,287 --> 00:07:01,967
I'll take you up.

137
00:07:02,446 --> 00:07:03,486
We'll take it from here.

138
00:07:04,366 --> 00:07:05,006
Okay.

139
00:07:06,087 --> 00:07:08,446
Did you know
Liu Jianyuan was a fugitive?

140
00:07:09,287 --> 00:07:10,366
I truly didn't know.

141
00:07:10,686 --> 00:07:13,126
I'd have reported him immediately
if I knew.

142
00:07:14,566 --> 00:07:15,847
What did he do this time?

143
00:07:18,287 --> 00:07:19,246
When did he contact you?

144
00:07:19,246 --> 00:07:20,006
And why?

145
00:07:20,006 --> 00:07:20,806
Officers,

146
00:07:21,006 --> 00:07:23,407
he called me before dawn
the day before yesterday.

147
00:07:23,806 --> 00:07:25,446
Said he came to Yunxi
for urgent business

148
00:07:25,967 --> 00:07:28,326
and needed a place
to stay after arriving.

149
00:07:28,566 --> 00:07:31,486
My old place's tenant just moved out.

150
00:07:31,767 --> 00:07:33,047
So I brought him here.

151
00:07:35,087 --> 00:07:36,446
You two are close, huh?

152
00:07:37,047 --> 00:07:38,767
N-not really, not really.

153
00:07:39,407 --> 00:07:41,847
He just looked out for me in prison.

154
00:07:42,126 --> 00:07:43,167
We got along okay.

155
00:07:43,686 --> 00:07:44,886
How did you find him dead?

156
00:07:45,126 --> 00:07:45,847
Officers,

157
00:07:47,006 --> 00:07:50,006
I planned to treat him to dinner.

158
00:07:50,446 --> 00:07:52,647
I called him multiple times.
But he didn't answer.

159
00:07:52,886 --> 00:07:54,246
I thought he was sleeping in.

160
00:07:54,246 --> 00:07:55,446
But then a whole day passed.

161
00:07:55,727 --> 00:07:57,287
I got worried and came to check.

162
00:07:57,486 --> 00:07:58,926
He didn't answer when I knocked.

163
00:07:59,446 --> 00:08:01,207
So I used the spare key.

164
00:08:01,366 --> 00:08:03,047
Right when I entered,

165
00:08:03,047 --> 00:08:05,607
I saw him lying there... dead.

166
00:08:39,247 --> 00:08:39,726
Get in.

167
00:08:39,726 --> 00:08:40,086
Yes.

168
00:08:44,726 --> 00:08:45,367
Captain Leng.

169
00:08:47,726 --> 00:08:48,446
Fifth floor.

170
00:08:52,127 --> 00:08:52,606
Ye.

171
00:09:29,887 --> 00:09:32,086
Tell us about your meeting
with Liu Jianyuan.

172
00:09:32,767 --> 00:09:33,487
Officers.

173
00:09:33,887 --> 00:09:38,047
He called me around 2 AM the night
before last, saying he was coming over.

174
00:09:38,206 --> 00:09:39,367
I live nearby,

175
00:09:39,367 --> 00:09:40,527
so I waited downstairs.

176
00:09:41,007 --> 00:09:42,806
I brought him up and chatted a bit.

177
00:09:43,287 --> 00:09:44,446
Then I went home.

178
00:09:44,966 --> 00:09:46,966
What was his condition then?

179
00:09:47,367 --> 00:09:48,206
Condition?

180
00:09:49,007 --> 00:09:50,007
Hard to say.

181
00:09:51,047 --> 00:09:52,007
Seemed nervous.

182
00:09:52,726 --> 00:09:54,007
Can't really put it into words.

183
00:09:55,287 --> 00:09:56,664
What did you do the last two days?

184
00:09:57,007 --> 00:09:58,086
Any alibis?

185
00:09:58,206 --> 00:09:59,047
Y-yes.

186
00:09:59,247 --> 00:10:01,167
My wife, kids,
and mother-in-law were home.

187
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:02,926
My wife was upset

188
00:10:02,926 --> 00:10:04,806
that I lent the place to a friend.

189
00:10:04,806 --> 00:10:06,407
We argued about it several times.

190
00:10:07,086 --> 00:10:09,047
We even called
the local police yesterday.

191
00:10:10,287 --> 00:10:12,287
For reformed people like me,

192
00:10:12,287 --> 00:10:13,407
trying to restart our lives,

193
00:10:13,966 --> 00:10:15,167
the government keeps watch...

194
00:10:15,446 --> 00:10:16,007
No.

195
00:10:16,007 --> 00:10:18,686
I mean, the government cares about us.

196
00:10:19,566 --> 00:10:21,287
Knowing they care about you,

197
00:10:21,606 --> 00:10:23,206
shouldn't you cooperate fully?

198
00:10:23,206 --> 00:10:23,647
Yes.

199
00:10:23,647 --> 00:10:24,247
Right?

200
00:10:24,247 --> 00:10:24,887
Right.

201
00:10:25,806 --> 00:10:28,287
So you were on good terms, yes?

202
00:10:28,487 --> 00:10:29,167
No.

203
00:10:29,566 --> 00:10:30,167
No.

204
00:10:30,606 --> 00:10:31,606
Long time no contact.

205
00:10:31,606 --> 00:10:32,487
What? What's going on?

206
00:10:33,527 --> 00:10:34,446
Not telling the truth?

207
00:10:35,167 --> 00:10:35,767
It's truth.

208
00:10:35,926 --> 00:10:36,887
In 2012,

209
00:10:37,446 --> 00:10:39,206
Liu Jianyuan got out, right?

210
00:10:39,206 --> 00:10:39,846
Right.

211
00:10:40,127 --> 00:10:41,326
He still had your number.

212
00:10:41,887 --> 00:10:43,966
He called you at midnight, and you went.

213
00:10:44,367 --> 00:10:46,407
You argued with your wife,
and despite that,

214
00:10:47,047 --> 00:10:49,167
you still lent your place to him.

215
00:10:49,367 --> 00:10:50,606
And you weren't on good terms?

216
00:10:51,767 --> 00:10:52,566
What?

217
00:10:53,007 --> 00:10:53,887
Want more jail time?

218
00:10:54,007 --> 00:10:55,966
No. I'll talk. I'll talk.

219
00:10:56,566 --> 00:10:57,887
We rarely contacted each other.

220
00:10:58,047 --> 00:10:59,887
Just exchanged greetings during holidays

221
00:11:00,367 --> 00:11:01,686
and chatted occasionally.

222
00:11:02,487 --> 00:11:05,367
Well, he did help me out
back in the day.

223
00:11:05,767 --> 00:11:07,367
A man should repay kindness, right?

224
00:11:07,566 --> 00:11:08,446
As the saying goes,

225
00:11:08,446 --> 00:11:09,846
more friends, more paths.

226
00:11:10,287 --> 00:11:13,686
I... I... I...

227
00:11:13,686 --> 00:11:14,487
Anything else?

228
00:11:14,487 --> 00:11:16,726
I hadn't seen him in years.

229
00:11:19,247 --> 00:11:20,487
When he first came in,

230
00:11:20,566 --> 00:11:22,407
there seemed to be something
on his sleeve.

231
00:11:23,487 --> 00:11:25,167
Looked... looked like blood.

232
00:11:25,527 --> 00:11:26,326
Go on.

233
00:11:26,407 --> 00:11:27,926
I asked him about it.

234
00:11:28,287 --> 00:11:31,326
He said he got into a fight
on the way over.

235
00:11:31,767 --> 00:11:33,726
I didn't dare ask any more.

236
00:11:35,007 --> 00:11:35,367
And?

237
00:11:35,367 --> 00:11:36,527
That's all?

238
00:11:37,367 --> 00:11:38,167
That's all.

239
00:11:38,487 --> 00:11:40,367
Really, nothing else.

240
00:11:44,206 --> 00:11:47,287
Liu Jianyuan's time of death
was between 4 AM and 5 AM yesterday.

241
00:11:48,527 --> 00:11:52,206
The COD was brain injury
caused by blunt head trauma.

242
00:11:53,407 --> 00:11:55,367
The murder weapon
was the vase found at the scene.

243
00:11:55,926 --> 00:11:59,767
Also, we found traces of Liu Min's blood
on Liu Jianyuan's coat.

244
00:12:04,647 --> 00:12:05,487
About the vase,

245
00:12:05,487 --> 00:12:06,647
we confirmed with the owner.

246
00:12:06,647 --> 00:12:08,367
It belonged to the place.

247
00:12:08,606 --> 00:12:09,287
No signs

248
00:12:09,287 --> 00:12:11,326
of forced entry were found at the scene.

249
00:12:11,326 --> 00:12:13,487
The place was always rented out.

250
00:12:13,487 --> 00:12:14,926
People came and went frequently.

251
00:12:15,206 --> 00:12:16,726
Fingerprints inside were quite messy.

252
00:12:16,726 --> 00:12:18,926
No valuable leads have been found yet.

253
00:12:19,326 --> 00:12:21,127
So, either the killer had a key

254
00:12:21,726 --> 00:12:23,527
or Liu Jianyuan opened the door himself.

255
00:12:23,726 --> 00:12:24,527
Hard to say.

256
00:12:28,206 --> 00:12:30,326
Liu Jianyuan wasn't local.

257
00:12:30,407 --> 00:12:31,367
He was a wanted man.

258
00:12:31,926 --> 00:12:34,606
Not many people knew he came to Yunxi.

259
00:12:35,167 --> 00:12:36,407
Could it be

260
00:12:36,566 --> 00:12:38,086
that Li Feng did it?

261
00:12:38,487 --> 00:12:39,446
We checked that.

262
00:12:39,647 --> 00:12:43,287
Li Feng hasn't had much contact
with Liu Jianyuan in recent years.

263
00:12:43,407 --> 00:12:44,686
He also lacks a motive.

264
00:12:46,487 --> 00:12:47,127
Captain Leng,

265
00:12:47,846 --> 00:12:50,407
Tech University Staff Community is old,

266
00:12:50,407 --> 00:12:53,726
but the surveillance
is better than we thought.

267
00:12:53,726 --> 00:12:55,966
The east, south, and north gates,

268
00:12:55,966 --> 00:12:58,806
and every building entrance,
have cameras.

269
00:13:00,767 --> 00:13:03,726
This is Liu Jianyuan
entering the community.

270
00:13:06,726 --> 00:13:12,367
This is the owner, Li Feng,
and Liu Jianyuan entering Building 17.

271
00:13:14,247 --> 00:13:16,647
Liu Jianyuan
entered the community at 3:10 AM.

272
00:13:17,487 --> 00:13:21,326
After Li Feng
went upstairs with Liu Jianyuan,

273
00:13:21,887 --> 00:13:23,167
he didn't stay long.

274
00:13:23,167 --> 00:13:25,086
It was about 15 minutes total.

275
00:13:25,806 --> 00:13:29,806
So Li Feng didn't have time
to commit the crime.

276
00:13:31,566 --> 00:13:35,287
Someone like Liu Jianyuan
must have pissed off plenty of people.

277
00:13:35,606 --> 00:13:37,926
Maybe there are others
we don't know about watching him.

278
00:13:39,367 --> 00:13:40,206
Jiao,

279
00:13:40,326 --> 00:13:43,726
did the entry or exit surveillance
catch anyone suspicious?

280
00:13:45,926 --> 00:13:51,407
From when Li Feng left at 3:30 AM
until 6:00 AM the next morning,

281
00:13:51,527 --> 00:13:53,086
when the first exerciser appeared,

282
00:13:53,086 --> 00:13:55,206
no one entered or exited
during that time.

283
00:13:57,127 --> 00:14:00,326
Then, from 6:00 AM,
when the exerciser came out,

284
00:14:00,326 --> 00:14:02,446
until Li Feng came here to report it

285
00:14:02,446 --> 00:14:03,407
and you arrived,

286
00:14:03,887 --> 00:14:06,686
apart from delivery
and takeout couriers,

287
00:14:07,446 --> 00:14:09,806
only residents of that building
came and went.

288
00:14:11,686 --> 00:14:13,686
Get the local police to assist

289
00:14:14,446 --> 00:14:16,566
in screening the residents
of Building 17

290
00:14:17,407 --> 00:14:20,407
and rechecking all the delivery
and takeout personnel

291
00:14:20,407 --> 00:14:21,527
who entered and exited.

292
00:14:22,367 --> 00:14:23,007
Okay.

293
00:14:27,606 --> 00:14:29,326
Liu Jianyuan killed Liu Min

294
00:14:29,326 --> 00:14:30,926
and then got killed by someone else.

295
00:14:31,127 --> 00:14:32,566
The timing is incredibly tight.

296
00:14:33,007 --> 00:14:35,566
But we still don't know
why Liu Jianyuan killed Liu Min.

297
00:14:35,966 --> 00:14:37,686
Neither phone was found at the scene.

298
00:14:38,127 --> 00:14:39,647
Could the killer have taken them?

299
00:14:40,726 --> 00:14:42,726
Liu Jianyuan
might not have killed Liu Min.

300
00:14:43,367 --> 00:14:44,167
Why?

301
00:14:44,806 --> 00:14:47,926
Current evidence shows only
that Liu Jianyuan and Liu Min fought.

302
00:14:48,806 --> 00:14:50,326
But there was a secondary blow,

303
00:14:50,806 --> 00:14:54,606
and Liu Jianyuan's coat showed no traces
of brain tissue or cerebrospinal fluid.

304
00:14:55,287 --> 00:14:56,326
From the surveillance,

305
00:14:56,326 --> 00:14:58,527
Liu Min packed fried leek-stuffed pastry
as takeout.

306
00:14:58,527 --> 00:14:59,846
But the autopsy results show

307
00:14:59,846 --> 00:15:02,407
no leeks in Liu Jianyuan
or Liu Min's stomach contents.

308
00:15:04,887 --> 00:15:05,887
Are you suggesting

309
00:15:05,887 --> 00:15:08,167
there was another person at the scene?

310
00:15:08,966 --> 00:15:09,726
And this person

311
00:15:09,726 --> 00:15:12,726
killed Liu Min after Liu Jianyuan fled

312
00:15:13,287 --> 00:15:16,407
and also ate fried leek-stuffed pastry?

313
00:15:16,647 --> 00:15:19,606
But the surveillance shows
no one else entered that room

314
00:15:19,606 --> 00:15:21,446
besides Liu Jianyuan and Liu Min.

315
00:15:21,726 --> 00:15:22,407
Exactly.

316
00:15:22,566 --> 00:15:24,487
So if this person really exists,

317
00:15:24,647 --> 00:15:26,127
did he scale walls

318
00:15:26,127 --> 00:15:27,206
or walk on clouds?

319
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:29,367
Is this Journey to the West?
Think he's Sun Wukong?

320
00:15:29,367 --> 00:15:30,686
Maybe Spider-Man?

321
00:15:30,846 --> 00:15:33,167
Enough joking. Be serious.

322
00:15:34,446 --> 00:15:38,206
Could the hotel's surveillance footage
be faulty?

323
00:15:38,446 --> 00:15:39,127
Master,

324
00:15:39,887 --> 00:15:41,784
in a case in the neighboring province
last year,

325
00:15:41,926 --> 00:15:45,127
the suspect entered through
the drainpipes to commit the crime.

326
00:15:45,487 --> 00:15:49,287
What if the suspect in this case
entered the hotel the same way?

327
00:16:06,767 --> 00:16:07,726
Is it sturdy enough?

328
00:16:07,726 --> 00:16:08,767
Can it hold?

329
00:16:08,767 --> 00:16:10,047
I don't want to get killed.

330
00:16:11,007 --> 00:16:11,606
Hurry up.

331
00:16:12,767 --> 00:16:13,566
Get moving.

332
00:16:15,487 --> 00:16:16,527
It's so high up.

333
00:16:18,086 --> 00:16:19,686
I barely got this borrowed. Hurry.

334
00:16:29,247 --> 00:16:30,086
Come on.

335
00:16:41,446 --> 00:16:42,247
Anything?

336
00:16:43,846 --> 00:16:44,446
No.

337
00:16:44,846 --> 00:16:45,487
Check higher up.

338
00:17:03,527 --> 00:17:04,166
Anything?

339
00:17:18,727 --> 00:17:19,886
- Anything here?
- Stop.

340
00:17:33,886 --> 00:17:34,767
Will it work?

341
00:17:35,326 --> 00:17:36,126
No problem.

342
00:17:36,767 --> 00:17:38,767
Modern drainpipes
are made of PVC material.

343
00:17:38,846 --> 00:17:39,646
Very slippery.

344
00:17:39,806 --> 00:17:40,927
Couldn't climb with gloves.

345
00:17:40,927 --> 00:17:42,126
So there must be fingerprints.

346
00:17:44,646 --> 00:17:48,166
Are the pipes at the Tech University
Staff Community also made of PVC?

347
00:17:55,207 --> 00:17:56,007
Yes.

348
00:17:57,326 --> 00:17:58,606
So we have to climb again?

349
00:18:02,086 --> 00:18:02,886
Master,

350
00:18:04,846 --> 00:18:07,126
at both crime scenes,

351
00:18:07,727 --> 00:18:11,166
climbing traces were found
on the external drainpipes.

352
00:18:11,527 --> 00:18:12,846
We've compared the fingerprints.

353
00:18:12,846 --> 00:18:13,927
They have the same owner.

354
00:18:13,927 --> 00:18:15,406
Currently known to be male,

355
00:18:15,406 --> 00:18:17,086
not tall, and slightly thin.

356
00:18:17,086 --> 00:18:18,566
Very likely a teenager.

357
00:18:18,687 --> 00:18:19,566
A teenager?

358
00:18:20,967 --> 00:18:21,527
Yes.

359
00:18:21,727 --> 00:18:23,967
Analysis of the fingerprint
ridge spacing indicates

360
00:18:23,967 --> 00:18:27,247
this person's fingerprints
are still in the developmental stage.

361
00:18:27,247 --> 00:18:28,687
He should be around 18 years old.

362
00:18:30,886 --> 00:18:34,566
Are you saying the suspect
for both cases is the same person?

363
00:18:35,047 --> 00:18:36,406
And a teenager?

364
00:18:36,406 --> 00:18:41,166
We can't yet confirm
the suspect is a teenager,

365
00:18:41,166 --> 00:18:42,646
but he was at both scenes.

366
00:18:42,886 --> 00:18:46,566
Fingerprints were found inside
and outside the entry window frames.

367
00:18:47,687 --> 00:18:49,927
I'll go cross-check

368
00:18:50,007 --> 00:18:53,527
the fingerprints found now
against all previously found ones.

369
00:18:53,527 --> 00:18:55,687
See if any matches come up.

370
00:18:55,687 --> 00:18:57,007
Let me catch my breath first.

371
00:18:57,007 --> 00:18:57,606
Also,

372
00:18:58,406 --> 00:19:04,126
here's the investigation into taxis
near Rose Garden Hotel post-incident.

373
00:19:04,727 --> 00:19:05,927
This taxi

374
00:19:07,326 --> 00:19:10,846
picked up a passenger around 2 AM
on the night of the crime.

375
00:19:11,126 --> 00:19:13,287
The driver said the passenger
seemed like a student.

376
00:19:13,287 --> 00:19:14,727
He was not tall, slightly thin,

377
00:19:14,846 --> 00:19:16,846
wearing sportswear,
and carrying a backpack.

378
00:19:16,846 --> 00:19:18,687
Also headed to
Tech University Staff Community.

379
00:19:24,247 --> 00:19:25,886
This is the surveillance footage

380
00:19:25,886 --> 00:19:28,606
from the community's east gate
during that time frame.

381
00:19:32,406 --> 00:19:35,366
This person
should match your description.

382
00:19:36,326 --> 00:19:37,487
Can we see his face clearly?

383
00:19:38,007 --> 00:19:39,447
No, this is the maximum zoom.

384
00:19:40,406 --> 00:19:43,366
Liu Jianyuan seeking refuge
with Li Feng was a sudden development.

385
00:19:43,487 --> 00:19:45,967
So how did this kid know
to come to this community?

386
00:19:47,007 --> 00:19:48,166
If he tailed Liu Jianyuan,

387
00:19:48,166 --> 00:19:49,287
timing-wise, it's unlikely.

388
00:19:49,527 --> 00:19:51,247
The taxi driver
didn't mention that either.

389
00:19:51,687 --> 00:19:54,126
So he must have gotten it from Liu Min.

390
00:19:54,566 --> 00:19:55,527
You're saying

391
00:19:55,527 --> 00:19:56,646
he interrogated Liu Min

392
00:19:56,646 --> 00:19:57,646
and killed her

393
00:19:57,646 --> 00:19:59,166
and then rushed to this community

394
00:19:59,166 --> 00:20:00,326
and killed Liu Jianyuan?

395
00:20:00,487 --> 00:20:02,687
Look at him. Does he even look 18?

396
00:20:03,007 --> 00:20:04,326
Could he pull that off?

397
00:20:04,447 --> 00:20:06,886
And what kind of deep hatred
would drive this?

398
00:20:07,247 --> 00:20:08,047
Jiao,

399
00:20:08,806 --> 00:20:10,447
find a way to enhance this image.

400
00:20:10,767 --> 00:20:14,007
Cross-reference it with the cases
Liu Jianyuan and Liu Min were in.

401
00:20:14,366 --> 00:20:15,687
Wait, you mean

402
00:20:15,767 --> 00:20:16,846
this kid...

403
00:20:17,366 --> 00:20:19,767
Unfortunately, we couldn't extract DNA
from the fingerprints.

404
00:20:26,727 --> 00:20:27,447
Hello?

405
00:20:28,846 --> 00:20:29,606
Son.

406
00:20:31,326 --> 00:20:32,287
You'll come tomorrow?

407
00:20:33,086 --> 00:20:34,126
Did your mother agree?

408
00:20:35,366 --> 00:20:36,646
Alright, okay.

409
00:20:36,646 --> 00:20:37,447
See you tomorrow.

410
00:20:43,886 --> 00:20:45,967
A package was found
at the city police entrance.

411
00:20:45,967 --> 00:20:48,047
It's addressed to the chief.

412
00:20:48,247 --> 00:20:50,086
We checked. Nothing dangerous.

413
00:20:50,086 --> 00:20:53,287
But it's related to your case.

414
00:20:54,166 --> 00:20:55,007
Two cell phones.

415
00:21:16,007 --> 00:21:16,846
Sweetie.

416
00:21:17,967 --> 00:21:19,007
Why are you here?

417
00:21:20,447 --> 00:21:21,487
Are you hungry?

418
00:21:23,287 --> 00:21:23,927
Let me see.

419
00:21:25,047 --> 00:21:25,846
What's wrong?

420
00:21:27,606 --> 00:21:28,806
Hungry? Come on.

421
00:21:29,207 --> 00:21:30,646
I'll feed you something.

422
00:21:31,406 --> 00:21:32,687
I've got tasty treats here.

423
00:21:33,606 --> 00:21:34,166
Come.

424
00:21:35,326 --> 00:21:36,086
Don't rush.

425
00:21:36,727 --> 00:21:37,366
Just a moment.

426
00:21:37,846 --> 00:21:38,447
Come here.

427
00:21:38,447 --> 00:21:39,846
Eat here. Come on.

428
00:21:41,447 --> 00:21:42,366
You look starved.

429
00:21:44,566 --> 00:21:46,447
Come to me anytime you're hungry.

430
00:21:47,166 --> 00:21:48,366
I'm never short on food.

431
00:21:48,366 --> 00:21:49,247
I've got everything.

432
00:22:03,846 --> 00:22:04,566
Captain Leng,

433
00:22:04,806 --> 00:22:06,727
Lei says the phone number
that sent the video

434
00:22:06,727 --> 00:22:08,207
should yield results tomorrow.

435
00:22:08,406 --> 00:22:09,007
Good.

436
00:22:10,527 --> 00:22:13,527
I heard Xiaoyu is coming tomorrow.

437
00:22:13,886 --> 00:22:15,846
Yeah, he's coming tomorrow.

438
00:22:16,166 --> 00:22:17,406
No one's watching him.

439
00:22:17,886 --> 00:22:18,806
I figured

440
00:22:19,166 --> 00:22:23,126
he could hang out
with you all at the station.

441
00:22:23,126 --> 00:22:24,527
Sure, we'll help watch him.

442
00:22:24,527 --> 00:22:25,086
Okay.

443
00:22:26,166 --> 00:22:28,927
When I pick up Xiaoyu tomorrow,

444
00:22:29,727 --> 00:22:31,126
if I'm not back,

445
00:22:31,487 --> 00:22:33,086
start the meeting once everyone's here.

446
00:22:36,366 --> 00:22:39,927
Child trafficking cases
have been spiking lately.

447
00:22:40,126 --> 00:22:42,207
Have you considered
bringing Xiaoyu to live with you?

448
00:22:42,207 --> 00:22:43,447
Wouldn't that be safer?

449
00:22:43,967 --> 00:22:46,606
Xiaoyu might be better off
with his mother.

450
00:22:46,606 --> 00:22:47,606
As you can see,

451
00:22:48,967 --> 00:22:50,007
I'm overwhelmed.

452
00:22:50,007 --> 00:22:51,447
I need to look after my dad too.

453
00:22:55,527 --> 00:22:56,406
I'll let you work.

454
00:23:03,704 --> 00:23:05,846
(West Exit)

455
00:23:05,846 --> 00:23:06,646
Today,

456
00:23:06,927 --> 00:23:09,166
we're walking to the station.

457
00:23:10,366 --> 00:23:11,767
To get some exercise.

458
00:23:11,767 --> 00:23:12,967
You need to lose some weight.

459
00:23:13,967 --> 00:23:14,646
Alright.

460
00:23:15,086 --> 00:23:16,207
What game are you playing?

461
00:23:16,767 --> 00:23:17,566
All kinds of games.

462
00:23:17,566 --> 00:23:18,767
You wouldn't understand.

463
00:23:18,846 --> 00:23:19,646
You know what?

464
00:23:19,687 --> 00:23:22,927
Officer Long at our station
is really good at them.

465
00:23:23,447 --> 00:23:24,727
I'll let him teach you sometime.

466
00:23:25,527 --> 00:23:26,126
Okay.

467
00:23:28,566 --> 00:23:29,166
Hello?

468
00:23:31,047 --> 00:23:32,007
I'll be right there.

469
00:23:33,047 --> 00:23:34,806
Have Ye start the meeting first.

470
00:23:35,126 --> 00:23:35,687
Got it.

471
00:23:36,287 --> 00:23:37,166
Okay. See you soon.

472
00:23:37,406 --> 00:23:38,606
Hurry. Run.

473
00:23:39,047 --> 00:23:40,247
Where are you off to?

474
00:23:40,247 --> 00:23:41,527
What's wrong with you?

475
00:23:43,287 --> 00:23:45,047
How dare you hit me!

476
00:23:45,047 --> 00:23:45,487
Get out!

477
00:23:45,767 --> 00:23:46,326
You!

478
00:23:48,606 --> 00:23:49,487
You actually hit me?

479
00:23:49,487 --> 00:23:50,287
Darn you!

480
00:23:51,007 --> 00:23:52,767
How dare you hit me!

481
00:23:52,767 --> 00:23:53,687
You hit me!

482
00:23:56,366 --> 00:23:57,086
How dare you!

483
00:23:57,487 --> 00:23:58,326
How dare you!

484
00:24:01,487 --> 00:24:03,487
This is a video from Liu Min's phone.

485
00:24:04,447 --> 00:24:08,967
It was sent to her
by an unregistered number.

486
00:24:10,007 --> 00:24:13,646
Likely filmed outside Room 601
at the Rose Garden Hotel.

487
00:24:14,207 --> 00:24:16,806
The person filming is probably
the one we're looking for.

488
00:24:25,086 --> 00:24:25,927
Who are you?

489
00:24:28,047 --> 00:24:30,646
Why... why did you hit me?

490
00:24:31,247 --> 00:24:32,126
Why did you hit me?

491
00:24:35,326 --> 00:24:36,646
Back in 2008.

492
00:24:37,967 --> 00:24:41,126
Baijia Village, Qili Town,
Renshan County.

493
00:24:46,366 --> 00:24:47,166
What?

494
00:24:48,247 --> 00:24:49,846
What 2008?

495
00:24:50,287 --> 00:24:51,207
I don't know.

496
00:24:51,207 --> 00:24:52,326
I don't know anything.

497
00:24:52,447 --> 00:24:58,447
A newborn baby was kidnapped.

498
00:24:59,247 --> 00:25:00,606
It was your doing.

499
00:25:04,447 --> 00:25:05,846
You... you're mistaken.

500
00:25:05,846 --> 00:25:06,606
You're mistaken.

501
00:25:06,606 --> 00:25:07,727
I didn't do that.

502
00:25:07,886 --> 00:25:09,166
Qili Town... Qili Town.

503
00:25:09,166 --> 00:25:10,846
That's my home. My home.

504
00:25:10,846 --> 00:25:12,406
Home... home.

505
00:25:20,646 --> 00:25:22,687
This video came
from Liu Jianyuan's phone.

506
00:25:23,166 --> 00:25:24,207
Like the previous one,

507
00:25:24,767 --> 00:25:26,247
it was sent from the same number.

508
00:25:26,846 --> 00:25:29,207
By accessing Liu Jianyuan's phone,

509
00:25:29,447 --> 00:25:31,047
we found his ticket purchase records.

510
00:25:31,287 --> 00:25:35,806
He came to the city lately with Liu Min,
who was impersonating Mai Qianqian.

511
00:25:36,166 --> 00:25:37,687
They likely conducted a transaction.

512
00:25:37,846 --> 00:25:41,207
Clues have been sent to colleagues
handling anti-human trafficking.

513
00:25:42,606 --> 00:25:44,927
The murder weapon
used to kill Liu Min, the ashtray,

514
00:25:45,406 --> 00:25:47,806
and the vase
at Liu Jianyuan's murder scene

515
00:25:47,806 --> 00:25:51,487
both had fingerprints
matching those on the outdoor drainpipe.

516
00:25:52,247 --> 00:25:55,366
The technical department is working
on enhancing the video quality.

517
00:25:56,247 --> 00:25:59,126
They're matching it against
the anti-trafficking database.

518
00:25:59,606 --> 00:26:00,967
Nothing has been found yet.

519
00:26:01,886 --> 00:26:03,967
About the Baijia Village
mentioned in the video,

520
00:26:04,606 --> 00:26:06,207
we also inquired of the local police.

521
00:26:06,287 --> 00:26:07,086
They said

522
00:26:07,846 --> 00:26:13,287
since around 2008, no child abductions
or missing children cases have occurred.

523
00:26:13,967 --> 00:26:15,447
No related reports filed either.

524
00:26:16,406 --> 00:26:18,047
A teenager did these?

525
00:26:18,646 --> 00:26:20,447
Are kids these days crazy?

526
00:26:21,247 --> 00:26:23,126
Could there be someone else behind it?

527
00:26:23,846 --> 00:26:26,727
Cases using teenagers as a front
aren't uncommon.

528
00:26:31,672 --> 00:26:34,907
(Yunxi Police Department)

529
00:27:04,606 --> 00:27:05,247
Hello?

530
00:27:05,886 --> 00:27:06,687
Chief Xu?

531
00:27:09,086 --> 00:27:10,846
I'm downstairs. The meeting?

532
00:27:11,366 --> 00:27:12,447
No one notified me.

533
00:27:13,967 --> 00:27:14,646
Okay.

534
00:27:15,606 --> 00:27:17,606
I'll be there on time. Don't worry.

535
00:27:19,886 --> 00:27:20,967
Alright, stop playing.

536
00:27:24,207 --> 00:27:24,886
How's it going?

537
00:27:25,566 --> 00:27:27,207
Captain Leng, perfect timing.

538
00:27:27,566 --> 00:27:31,086
I rechecked the food containers
from Rose Garden Hotel.

539
00:27:31,086 --> 00:27:32,007
I found

540
00:27:32,007 --> 00:27:33,326
that kid's fingerprints on them.

541
00:27:33,326 --> 00:27:36,126
He was peeping, attacking,
and recording a video

542
00:27:36,606 --> 00:27:38,166
and still found time to eat.

543
00:27:38,166 --> 00:27:38,886
He's something.

544
00:27:39,566 --> 00:27:40,967
Does Ye Qian know?

545
00:27:40,967 --> 00:27:41,727
Told them.

546
00:27:44,086 --> 00:27:44,727
Son.

547
00:27:45,566 --> 00:27:46,247
Son.

548
00:27:46,527 --> 00:27:47,207
Come in.

549
00:27:47,967 --> 00:27:49,727
His mom's got some things
these few days.

550
00:27:49,846 --> 00:27:52,207
She asked me to watch him
for a couple of days.

551
00:27:52,806 --> 00:27:53,646
Say hello.

552
00:27:53,886 --> 00:27:54,646
Hello, everyone.

553
00:27:54,646 --> 00:27:55,767
What greeting is that?

554
00:27:56,247 --> 00:27:57,487
Address them properly.

555
00:27:58,247 --> 00:27:59,086
Uncle Jiao.

556
00:27:59,207 --> 00:28:00,207
Grandpa Jiao.

557
00:28:00,846 --> 00:28:01,927
Okay, that's enough.

558
00:28:01,967 --> 00:28:02,967
He can just stay with us.

559
00:28:02,967 --> 00:28:03,886
You go do your thing.

560
00:28:03,886 --> 00:28:05,007
Got a meeting in the city.

561
00:28:05,007 --> 00:28:05,527
Okay.

562
00:28:06,166 --> 00:28:07,086
Watch him for me.

563
00:28:07,247 --> 00:28:07,806
Okay.

564
00:28:07,806 --> 00:28:08,846
Less gaming.

565
00:28:08,846 --> 00:28:09,767
More reading.

566
00:28:10,047 --> 00:28:10,646
You hear me?

567
00:28:10,646 --> 00:28:11,247
Okay.

568
00:28:15,287 --> 00:28:17,326
Need to look into this more.

569
00:28:40,287 --> 00:28:40,967
We're here.

570
00:28:45,886 --> 00:28:46,727
- Hello.
- Hello.

571
00:28:46,727 --> 00:28:47,326
Thank you.

572
00:28:47,727 --> 00:28:48,287
Hello.

573
00:28:48,687 --> 00:28:49,247
This way.

574
00:28:49,487 --> 00:28:50,047
Okay.

575
00:28:55,767 --> 00:28:57,326
I've said this many times already.

576
00:28:57,967 --> 00:28:59,086
Nothing like that happened.

577
00:29:00,646 --> 00:29:03,566
We've never had
any missing children here.

578
00:29:03,806 --> 00:29:04,606
Have some water.

579
00:29:05,447 --> 00:29:07,086
Seems like you came for nothing.

580
00:29:07,366 --> 00:29:08,846
Please, think carefully again.

581
00:29:09,287 --> 00:29:10,447
No need to think anymore.

582
00:29:10,927 --> 00:29:12,566
It's such a small place.

583
00:29:13,126 --> 00:29:16,086
Do you think I wouldn't know
about every household?

584
00:29:18,606 --> 00:29:21,007
Please look at these two people.
Have you seen them?

585
00:29:23,086 --> 00:29:23,886
Haven't seen them.

586
00:29:26,927 --> 00:29:27,806
What about him?

587
00:29:30,806 --> 00:29:31,606
Don't know him.

588
00:29:33,566 --> 00:29:36,527
Cooperating with police investigations
is every citizen's duty.

589
00:29:36,527 --> 00:29:38,447
You're the village Party secretary
and a member.

590
00:29:38,886 --> 00:29:40,487
I shouldn't need to say more.

591
00:29:41,727 --> 00:29:44,326
Hey, who are you trying to scare,
young man?

592
00:29:47,646 --> 00:29:48,687
Who am I trying to scare?

593
00:29:49,126 --> 00:29:51,727
This case involves a fugitive
with a warrant.

594
00:29:52,326 --> 00:29:54,967
If you maintain
this uncooperative attitude,

595
00:29:55,687 --> 00:29:59,527
then we have reason
to suspect you're harboring a suspect.

596
00:30:08,886 --> 00:30:11,566
Well... that kid
really did something wrong?

597
00:30:21,007 --> 00:30:21,646
Here.

598
00:30:28,326 --> 00:30:30,606
It's not that I deliberately wanted
to hide it from you.

599
00:30:31,126 --> 00:30:31,927
About this matter,

600
00:30:32,566 --> 00:30:34,927
how do I put it... it's a family shame.

601
00:30:35,326 --> 00:30:38,927
Everyone in the village is related.
It doesn't sound good.

602
00:31:11,126 --> 00:31:12,366
(I saw him alone,)

603
00:31:12,566 --> 00:31:13,646
(and he didn't look well.)

604
00:31:14,326 --> 00:31:15,646
So I went over to ask.

605
00:31:16,767 --> 00:31:18,047
When I went up and took a look,

606
00:31:18,767 --> 00:31:21,767
that kid was definitely a Bai.

607
00:31:22,527 --> 00:31:26,487
His eyes and brows
looked exactly like Bai Youfu's.

608
00:31:26,927 --> 00:31:28,326
What's the deal with this family?

609
00:31:29,287 --> 00:31:30,687
The household head is Bai Shengguo.

610
00:31:31,126 --> 00:31:32,767
Youfu is their youngest son.

611
00:31:33,166 --> 00:31:34,967
He has an older brother and sister.

612
00:31:34,967 --> 00:31:36,247
They've all moved out.

613
00:31:36,727 --> 00:31:39,326
The youngest son stayed
to care for the ancestral home.

614
00:31:40,086 --> 00:31:42,287
So I took the kid home
to stay the night.

615
00:31:42,287 --> 00:31:44,166
I wanted to find out
what was really going on.

616
00:31:45,566 --> 00:31:47,406
The kid said his name

617
00:31:48,326 --> 00:31:49,447
was Ning Haiyang.

618
00:31:49,447 --> 00:31:50,326
Yeah, Ning Haiyang.

619
00:31:50,727 --> 00:31:52,927
He was snatched by traffickers
soon after he was born.

620
00:31:53,326 --> 00:31:56,487
A couple from the neighboring province
adopted him soon after.

621
00:31:56,927 --> 00:32:00,126
His adoptive dad
died in an accident early on.

622
00:32:00,326 --> 00:32:02,008
His adoptive mom
soon died of illness too.

623
00:32:02,566 --> 00:32:03,727
His adoptive relatives

624
00:32:03,727 --> 00:32:06,126
didn't treat him like family.

625
00:32:06,126 --> 00:32:07,406
He wasn't biologically related.

626
00:32:07,406 --> 00:32:08,886
So they pretty much ignored him.

627
00:32:09,527 --> 00:32:12,527
So the kid decided
to go find his birth parents.

628
00:32:13,047 --> 00:32:13,846
You know what?

629
00:32:14,326 --> 00:32:15,287
Somehow,

630
00:32:15,927 --> 00:32:17,007
he actually found them.

631
00:32:17,566 --> 00:32:19,727
His father is Bai Youfu.

632
00:32:21,767 --> 00:32:23,806
Why didn't the Bai family
report the child missing?

633
00:32:27,527 --> 00:32:29,007
Missing? No child went missing.

634
00:32:29,166 --> 00:32:31,086
That kid wasn't missing at all.

635
00:32:34,126 --> 00:32:34,927
He wasn't missing?

636
00:32:38,727 --> 00:32:40,806
Bai Youfu was working away from home,

637
00:32:40,806 --> 00:32:42,927
met a girl and started dating her.

638
00:32:43,487 --> 00:32:46,646
They got carried away,
and she ended up pregnant.

639
00:32:47,366 --> 00:32:49,927
Now with a baby on the way,
marriage was the next step, right?

640
00:32:51,287 --> 00:32:52,687
The girl demanded a betrothal gift.

641
00:32:53,767 --> 00:32:55,366
Youfu's brother had just gotten married.

642
00:32:55,927 --> 00:32:56,886
They'd thrown a feast

643
00:32:57,247 --> 00:32:58,207
and built a new house.

644
00:32:58,566 --> 00:33:00,086
The debts hadn't been paid off.

645
00:33:00,287 --> 00:33:02,287
They had no money
for Youfu's betrothal gift.

646
00:33:03,366 --> 00:33:04,646
Well, you know what?

647
00:33:05,166 --> 00:33:06,687
Youfu found a way himself.

648
00:33:07,247 --> 00:33:09,326
He gave the baby up for adoption

649
00:33:09,527 --> 00:33:12,566
and used the money from that adoption
for the betrothal gift.

650
00:33:13,366 --> 00:33:14,606
So according to you,

651
00:33:15,047 --> 00:33:16,927
the kid was sold by Bai Youfu himself?

652
00:33:17,326 --> 00:33:18,326
It wasn't selling.

653
00:33:19,886 --> 00:33:20,806
It was giving him away.

654
00:33:21,886 --> 00:33:23,326
That's a nice way to put it.

655
00:33:23,447 --> 00:33:26,086
Parents selling their own child
is still illegal.

656
00:33:28,927 --> 00:33:30,606
After Bai Youfu 'gave the child away',

657
00:33:31,126 --> 00:33:32,606
didn't his wife have any objections?

658
00:33:33,606 --> 00:33:34,326
From what I heard,

659
00:33:34,326 --> 00:33:36,047
they both planned it

660
00:33:36,047 --> 00:33:37,687
together.

661
00:33:39,687 --> 00:33:43,047
Life was already tough enough
for Youfu and his wife.

662
00:33:43,047 --> 00:33:45,247
They didn't have the energy
or money to care for a baby.

663
00:33:47,086 --> 00:33:48,166
Did Ning Haiyang know?

664
00:33:48,527 --> 00:33:49,967
Probably not.

665
00:33:50,886 --> 00:33:53,687
How could they tell their own child
something like that?

666
00:33:56,447 --> 00:33:58,366
The Bai family
was struggling financially.

667
00:33:59,646 --> 00:34:02,126
Bai Shengguo had to manage
what little land was left,

668
00:34:02,326 --> 00:34:04,447
take care of his elderly mother,

669
00:34:04,447 --> 00:34:06,606
and help raise his grandchildren.

670
00:34:06,727 --> 00:34:10,527
He lacked both the money and energy
for a kid appearing unexpectedly.

671
00:34:11,447 --> 00:34:13,566
The eldest Bai son
avoided his brother's troubles.

672
00:34:13,927 --> 00:34:17,527
And Bai Youfu himself
was under a lot of pressure.

673
00:34:18,126 --> 00:34:19,928
He and his current wife
had a baby last year.

674
00:34:20,086 --> 00:34:22,726
He did marry that girl he got pregnant,

675
00:34:22,766 --> 00:34:24,766
but they divorced
within a couple of years.

676
00:34:25,527 --> 00:34:28,126
His then remarried his current wife.

677
00:34:30,527 --> 00:34:33,166
When was the last time Ning Haiyang
came back to the village?

678
00:34:34,566 --> 00:34:35,847
About half a year ago.

679
00:34:36,606 --> 00:34:37,286
Yeah.

680
00:34:38,086 --> 00:34:40,407
I even let him stay at my place
for a night.

681
00:35:02,766 --> 00:35:06,447
I figured I'd find some time
to take him over

682
00:35:07,206 --> 00:35:11,126
to the Bai family
to ask some questions and talk it out.

683
00:35:11,527 --> 00:35:13,807
But the Bai family
wouldn't even open their door.

684
00:35:14,206 --> 00:35:15,246
I couldn't do much.

685
00:35:15,566 --> 00:35:17,967
I couldn't exactly force them out.

686
00:35:18,967 --> 00:35:21,246
The poor kid felt hopeless.

687
00:35:21,487 --> 00:35:22,807
So he just took off.

688
00:35:23,286 --> 00:35:25,246
Ning Haiyang is still a minor.

689
00:35:25,246 --> 00:35:26,887
And you just let him leave?

690
00:35:27,047 --> 00:35:29,686
Well, he came here on his own.

691
00:35:30,646 --> 00:35:31,686
That boy is tall,

692
00:35:32,367 --> 00:35:33,447
very mature for his age.

693
00:35:33,847 --> 00:35:36,047
He looks practically like an adult.

694
00:35:36,646 --> 00:35:37,967
And he knows how to fight.

695
00:35:38,527 --> 00:35:39,246
Oh yeah,

696
00:35:39,286 --> 00:35:41,047
there are dents on the tree in my yard

697
00:35:41,047 --> 00:35:42,726
from him practicing.

698
00:35:44,086 --> 00:35:46,047
I figured he'd be fine.

699
00:35:46,487 --> 00:35:49,047
Kids roughhousing a bit
shouldn't be a problem.

700
00:35:49,447 --> 00:35:53,246
He's probably gone back
to his adoptive relatives by now.

701
00:35:54,007 --> 00:35:57,686
Do you know where Bai Youfu
and his ex-wife are now?

702
00:35:58,166 --> 00:35:59,807
I'm not sure about his ex-wife.

703
00:36:00,367 --> 00:36:04,126
But Bai Youfu and his current wife
got a big rig, doing long-haul trucking.

704
00:36:04,686 --> 00:36:06,007
He just left a few days ago.

705
00:36:17,086 --> 00:36:17,887
Kid,

706
00:36:18,286 --> 00:36:20,007
it's time to eat.

707
00:36:20,007 --> 00:36:20,766
What'd you like?

708
00:36:20,766 --> 00:36:21,807
I will buy it for you.

709
00:36:22,047 --> 00:36:22,766
No need.

710
00:36:23,286 --> 00:36:24,807
I'll just order takeout myself.

711
00:36:25,646 --> 00:36:26,447
KFC.

712
00:36:27,246 --> 00:36:28,447
What would you like?

713
00:36:28,447 --> 00:36:29,166
My treat.

714
00:36:31,126 --> 00:36:32,246
You're pretty loaded, huh?

715
00:36:32,246 --> 00:36:33,126
Quite well-off.

716
00:36:33,606 --> 00:36:35,126
Not rich, just getting by.

717
00:36:35,807 --> 00:36:37,487
What have you been up to?

718
00:36:37,487 --> 00:36:38,246
Let me see.

719
00:36:39,166 --> 00:36:40,407
Look. Sudoku.

720
00:36:41,646 --> 00:36:42,447
Impressive.

721
00:36:42,606 --> 00:36:44,286
No wonder your parents don't nag you.

722
00:36:45,246 --> 00:36:46,766
As long as my grades don't slip.

723
00:36:46,887 --> 00:36:48,126
My dad can't understand it.

724
00:36:49,407 --> 00:36:51,246
Perfect, I have this too.

725
00:36:51,566 --> 00:36:54,246
I remember
there's an online versus mode.

726
00:36:54,246 --> 00:36:55,246
Let's have a match.

727
00:36:55,407 --> 00:36:56,206
Okay.

728
00:36:57,487 --> 00:36:58,887
Long, really?

729
00:36:58,887 --> 00:37:00,726
Why are you competing with a kid?

730
00:37:01,487 --> 00:37:02,566
With your gaming skills,

731
00:37:02,566 --> 00:37:04,407
aren't you just bullying him?

732
00:37:04,967 --> 00:37:05,766
It's fine.

733
00:37:06,246 --> 00:37:08,286
But if we're playing games
during your work hours,

734
00:37:08,286 --> 00:37:09,726
won't my dad get mad?

735
00:37:10,086 --> 00:37:12,166
No, it's lunch break.

736
00:37:12,807 --> 00:37:13,447
Go online.

737
00:37:13,686 --> 00:37:14,447
Okay.

738
00:37:19,967 --> 00:37:21,086
- Next to three.
- Long, over here.

739
00:37:21,086 --> 00:37:21,847
Left, left.

740
00:37:21,847 --> 00:37:22,606
- Three.
- Right, right.

741
00:37:22,606 --> 00:37:23,646
Stop talking.

742
00:37:23,686 --> 00:37:25,246
You're way too slow.

743
00:37:25,246 --> 00:37:26,246
- Nice.
- One row left.

744
00:37:26,807 --> 00:37:27,286
Check it.

745
00:37:27,286 --> 00:37:28,047
Here, here.

746
00:37:28,047 --> 00:37:29,527
And this cell.

747
00:37:29,566 --> 00:37:31,887
- Right.
- The cell on the right. Yes.

748
00:37:32,887 --> 00:37:33,566
Look.

749
00:37:33,646 --> 00:37:34,447
I won.

750
00:37:34,447 --> 00:37:35,686
Not bad, Xiaoyu.

751
00:37:35,686 --> 00:37:36,407
You beat Long.

752
00:37:36,407 --> 00:37:37,646
Shut up, okay?

753
00:37:37,646 --> 00:37:38,407
One more round.

754
00:37:38,407 --> 00:37:40,327
Best of five. I'm done.

755
00:37:40,407 --> 00:37:41,726
Aren't you embarrassed?

756
00:37:42,166 --> 00:37:43,847
Alright, break it up.

757
00:37:43,847 --> 00:37:44,487
Break it up.

758
00:37:44,487 --> 00:37:45,646
Can't handle losing?

759
00:37:46,566 --> 00:37:48,086
Win some, lose some. It's normal.

760
00:37:48,086 --> 00:37:50,047
Uncle Long,
you're not a sore loser, are you?

761
00:37:53,766 --> 00:37:55,086
You're a lot like your dad.

762
00:37:56,847 --> 00:37:58,086
I don't want to be like him.

763
00:37:58,766 --> 00:37:59,807
Why not?

764
00:38:00,086 --> 00:38:01,246
Your dad is amazing.

765
00:38:01,246 --> 00:38:03,646
He's the best cop
in our city and our province.

766
00:38:04,166 --> 00:38:06,086
I don't know
whether he's a great cop or not.

767
00:38:06,086 --> 00:38:07,686
Anyway, he's not a good dad.

768
00:38:08,286 --> 00:38:09,327
Xiaoyu,

769
00:38:09,327 --> 00:38:11,047
your dad cares about you a lot.

770
00:38:11,246 --> 00:38:12,606
You've misunderstood him.

771
00:38:14,447 --> 00:38:15,447
Auntie Ziwu,

772
00:38:15,807 --> 00:38:17,447
I know you have feelings for my dad.

773
00:38:18,166 --> 00:38:20,327
If my dad agrees, I have no objections.

774
00:38:21,166 --> 00:38:22,847
But I advise you to think carefully.

775
00:38:23,566 --> 00:38:25,847
'Think carefully'? 'Think carefully'?

776
00:38:26,007 --> 00:38:27,766
Is that something
a kid like you should say?

777
00:38:32,367 --> 00:38:33,447
Don't eat takeout.

778
00:38:34,246 --> 00:38:35,286
I bought you a meal.

779
00:38:35,286 --> 00:38:35,967
Have some.

780
00:38:35,967 --> 00:38:36,726
Okay, thank you.

781
00:38:38,047 --> 00:38:38,847
Spoon.

782
00:38:49,566 --> 00:38:50,606
- Captain Leng.
- Captain Leng.

783
00:38:50,847 --> 00:38:51,766
Okay, got it.

784
00:38:53,246 --> 00:38:53,887
- Captain Leng.
- Master.

785
00:38:54,206 --> 00:38:55,606
We got in touch with Bai Youfu.

786
00:38:55,646 --> 00:38:57,246
He's on the Qinghai-Xizang route.

787
00:38:57,487 --> 00:38:59,847
He said Ning Haiyang
came looking for him again later.

788
00:38:59,847 --> 00:39:01,887
Also, Bai Youfu admitted

789
00:39:02,246 --> 00:39:05,606
he previously sold the kid
through Liu Min and Liu Jianyuan.

790
00:39:06,407 --> 00:39:08,566
He wanted to get rid
of Ning Haiyang's pestering.

791
00:39:08,566 --> 00:39:10,086
So he told Ning Haiyang about this.

792
00:39:10,086 --> 00:39:11,246
But he didn't tell the truth.

793
00:39:11,246 --> 00:39:13,407
Instead, he told Ning Haiyang
those two kidnapped him.

794
00:39:14,646 --> 00:39:17,527
So Ning Haiyang's motive was revenge?

795
00:39:18,206 --> 00:39:18,887
Possibly.

796
00:39:19,126 --> 00:39:20,847
Also, Bai Youfu said

797
00:39:21,407 --> 00:39:23,286
Ning Haiyang's biological mother
is in Yunxi.

798
00:39:23,487 --> 00:39:24,967
Maybe Ning Haiyang will go find her.

799
00:39:24,967 --> 00:39:26,686
You two,
look into Xiao Lan's whereabouts.

800
00:39:26,686 --> 00:39:27,206
Go.

801
00:39:27,206 --> 00:39:27,807
Yes.

802
00:39:27,807 --> 00:39:28,246
Yes.

803
00:39:28,246 --> 00:39:30,286
Young people nowadays are so impulsive.

804
00:39:30,286 --> 00:39:31,126
He's really only 18?

805
00:39:31,126 --> 00:39:31,927
You just graduated.

806
00:39:31,927 --> 00:39:33,206
Don't be like that.

807
00:39:33,206 --> 00:39:34,327
You sound like my dad.

808
00:39:35,320 --> 00:39:35,800
(Dan Qing)

809
00:39:38,872 --> 00:39:40,216
(Dan Qing)

810
00:39:41,807 --> 00:39:42,407
Sorry.

811
00:39:42,646 --> 00:39:44,887
The number you dialed is busy.

812
00:39:45,007 --> 00:39:46,246
Please try again later.

813
00:40:00,086 --> 00:40:01,206
So many shops.

814
00:40:02,166 --> 00:40:04,184
Xiao Lan's stall
is in the small commodities area.

815
00:40:04,327 --> 00:40:06,086
But at this hour, might it be closed?

816
00:40:06,086 --> 00:40:07,086
Let's take a look first.

817
00:40:14,456 --> 00:40:26,645
(Dan Qing, is everything going well?
When is the delivery?)

818
00:40:28,887 --> 00:40:30,887
These storefronts all look the same.

819
00:40:31,807 --> 00:40:34,007
Pay attention to her unit number, D1023.

820
00:40:34,047 --> 00:40:35,527
D1023.

821
00:40:36,367 --> 00:40:37,007
Okay.

822
00:40:47,245 --> 00:40:52,636
(Guangchang Mall)

823
00:40:53,007 --> 00:40:54,286
D1023. This is it.

824
00:41:02,246 --> 00:41:03,206
Are you Xiao Lan?

825
00:41:05,847 --> 00:41:08,047
I am. Who are you?

826
00:41:08,527 --> 00:41:10,246
We're from the Yunxi CID.

827
00:41:10,566 --> 00:41:11,646
Here are our IDs.

828
00:41:15,606 --> 00:41:16,606
Don't be nervous.

829
00:41:24,847 --> 00:41:25,646
Ning Haiyang.

830
00:41:31,206 --> 00:41:32,007
Don't panic.

831
00:41:38,606 --> 00:41:41,047
Ning Haiyang ran east
along the riverbank!

832
00:41:41,047 --> 00:41:41,646
After him!

833
00:41:49,407 --> 00:41:50,487
- Stop!
- Stop!

834
00:42:08,280 --> 00:42:08,927
What happened?

835
00:42:08,927 --> 00:42:09,686
You, go that way.

836
00:42:22,246 --> 00:42:22,807
Stop!

837
00:42:26,648 --> 00:42:30,141
♪Replacing the weight of tears
with that of sweat♪

838
00:42:33,935 --> 00:42:39,256
♪Covering the gunshot's sound
with wounds♪

839
00:42:41,329 --> 00:42:46,183
♪No one is born unyielding and strong♪

840
00:42:46,989 --> 00:42:50,136
♪But because someone
always rushes ahead♪

841
00:42:50,136 --> 00:42:53,240
♪To shield us from the storm♪

842
00:42:55,896 --> 00:43:01,030
♪When every extraordinary act
becomes routine♪

843
00:43:03,000 --> 00:43:08,632
♪Just to polish the badge
upon their shoulder♪

844
00:43:10,392 --> 00:43:13,976
♪Like light surging unseen
through the night♪

845
00:43:15,128 --> 00:43:22,568
♪Converging into your form♪

846
00:43:23,000 --> 00:43:25,678
♪Looking up♪

847
00:43:25,678 --> 00:43:29,217
♪Such dazzling glory♪

848
00:43:30,200 --> 00:43:32,760
♪Like hope♪

849
00:43:32,760 --> 00:43:36,693
♪Reaching out its arms♪

850
00:43:37,560 --> 00:43:40,212
♪Cloaked in light♪

851
00:43:40,212 --> 00:43:44,696
♪Alone, they charge ahead♪

852
00:43:44,696 --> 00:43:47,512
♪Traversing♪

853
00:43:47,512 --> 00:43:54,023
♪The battlefield of fate♪
